WEBVTT

00:04:58.020 --> 00:05:00.943
That's a National Geographic image

00:05:00.967 --> 00:05:04.086
of what is called the mammoth steppe,

00:05:04.635 --> 00:05:08.394
what the far north, the sub-Arctic
and Arctic region, used to look like.

00:05:08.824 --> 00:05:11.720
In fact, the whole world
used to look like that.

00:05:12.260 --> 00:05:15.596
What we find in South Africa
and the Serengeti now,

00:05:15.620 --> 00:05:17.254
lots of big animals,

00:05:17.278 --> 00:05:20.650
was the case in this part of Canada,

00:05:20.674 --> 00:05:23.614
throughout the US, throughout Eurasia,
throughout the world.

00:05:23.638 --> 00:05:24.841
This was the norm

00:05:25.350 --> 00:05:27.588
and can be again.

00:05:28.470 --> 00:05:30.311
So in a sense,